President Donald J. Trump has appointed Dr. Charles M. Kupperman as Assistant to the President and Deputy National Security Advisor. Dr. Kupperman has over four decades of experience in national security policy and programs, having served in various positions in the Reagan Administration, including in the Executive Office of the President and the National Aeronautics and Space Administration. He also worked as a Defense and Foreign Policy Advisor to the Ronald Reagan Presidential campaign. Dr. Kupperman's expertise in defense, arms control, and aerospace will contribute to President Trump's national security agenda. He previously held positions at Boeing and Lockheed Martin Corporation and holds a Ph.D. in Strategic Studies from the University of Southern California.